HEADWORD: Disulphide
<hw>Di*sul"phide</hw> <pr>(?; 104)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>sulphide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
binary compound of sulphur containing two atoms of sulphur in each
molecule; -- formerly called <xex>disulphuret</xex>. Cf.
<er>Bisulphide</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disulphuret</ent>⟦br⟧
